        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which AI builders integrate best with SaaS tools?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "For SaaS-specific integrations, here's what works: (1) Framerâ€”best for modern stacks, connects to Stripe (payments), Mailchimp/ConvertKit (email), Typeform (surveys), Zapier (2000+ apps), and exports clean React code for custom integrations. (2) Webflowâ€”most powerful CMS, integrates with HubSpot, Marketo, Salesforce CRM, MemberStack for user accounts, and has API for custom backend connections. (3) Mixoâ€”simplest integrations: Mailchimp, Google Analytics, Facebook Pixel. Good enough for early-stage, limited for growth. (4) 10Web/WordPressâ€”60,000+ plugins including every SaaS tool imaginable, but requires WordPress maintenance. For SaaS startups, prioritize: email capture (Mailchimp/ConvertKit), analytics (Google Analytics 4, Mixpanel), payments (Stripe, Paddle), and CRM (HubSpot if B2B enterprise). Most early-stage SaaS don't need complex integrationsâ€”email capture and Stripe cover 80% of use cases. Add more as you scale. Integration complexity should match revenue complexity, not engineering ambition."
        }
      }
    ]}
